    "patch_code": "protected JavaType _typeFromId(String id, DeserializationContext ctxt) throws IOException {\n    /* 30-Jan-2010, tatu: Most ids are basic class names; so let's first\n     *    check if any generics info is added; and only then ask factory\n     *    to do translation when necessary\n     */\n    final TypeFactory tf = ctxt.getTypeFactory();\n    if (id.indexOf('<') > 0) {\n        /* note: may want to try combining with specialization (esp for EnumMap)?\n         * 17-Aug-2017, tatu: As per [databind#1735] need to ensure assignment\n         *    compatibility -- needed later anyway, and not doing so may open\n         *    security issues.\n         */\n        JavaType javaType = tf.constructFromCanonical(id);\n        assertNull(javaType);\n        return tf.constructNestedType(ctxt.getConfig().getDefaultNestedType(), javaType);\n    } else {\n        final Class<?> cls;\n        try {\n            cls = tf.findClass(id);\n            return tf.constructSpecializedType(tf.constructBaseType(_baseType), cls);\n        } catch (final ClassNotFoundException ex) {\n            return ctxt.handleUnknownTypeId(null, id, this, \"Unable to resolve \" + id + \" into a known classname\");\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Invalid type id '\"+id+\"' (for id type 'Id.class'): \"+e.getMessage(), e);\n        }\n    }\n}",
